.TH OPENTELEMETRY-PYTHON 8 "@DATE@" "opentelemetry-python-autoinstrumentation @VERSION@" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
opentelemetry-python \- OpenTelemetry Python Auto-Instrumentation
.SH SYNOPSIS
Python auto-instrumentation is activated automatically by the OpenTelemetry Injector
via
.B PYTHONPATH
when a Python 3.10+ application starts.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The OpenTelemetry Python Auto-Instrumentation automatically instruments Python
applications to collect distributed traces, metrics, and logs without requiring
code changes.
.PP
When used with the OpenTelemetry Injector package, the injector prepends
.I /usr/lib/opentelemetry/python
to
.B PYTHONPATH
for every process. Python then automatically executes the
.B sitecustomize.py
module found there before the application starts. That module performs safety checks
(Python version, OTLP protocol, double-instrumentation, dependency conflicts) and, if
all pass, calls
.B opentelemetry.instrumentation.auto_instrumentation.initialize()
to activate all discovered instrumentation plug-ins.
.PP
The package bundles the
.B opentelemetry-exporter-otlp-pyproto-http
exporter, a pure-Python protobuf implementation that carries no C-extension
dependency on
.B google-protobuf
and therefore avoids version conflicts with application dependencies.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /usr/lib/opentelemetry/python/sitecustomize.py
Auto-instrumentation entry point, executed by Python at startup.
.TP
.B /usr/lib/opentelemetry/python/all-dependencies.txt
Pinned dependency manifest used at runtime to detect version conflicts.
.TP
.B /etc/opentelemetry/python/otel-config.yaml
Optional declarative configuration file.
.TP
.B /etc/opentelemetry/injector/conf.d/python.conf
Drop-in configuration file that registers the Python agent path with the injector.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B OTEL_SERVICE_NAME
Set the service name for telemetry data.
.TP
.B OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT
Set the OTLP exporter endpoint (e.g., http://localhost:4318).
.TP
.B OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_PROTOCOL
Must be set to
.B http/protobuf
or
.B http/json
(grpc is not supported by this package).
.TP
.B OTEL_TRACES_EXPORTER
Set the traces exporter (default: otlp_pyproto_http).
.TP
.B OTEL_METRICS_EXPORTER
Set the metrics exporter (default: otlp_pyproto_http).
.TP
.B OTEL_LOGS_EXPORTER
Set the logs exporter (default: otlp_pyproto_http).
.TP
.B OTEL_PYTHON_DISABLED_INSTRUMENTATIONS
Comma-separated list of instrumentation packages to disable.
.TP
.B OTEL_INJECTOR_LOG_LEVEL
Set to
.B debug
to enable verbose logging from sitecustomize.py.
.TP
.B OTEL_EXPERIMENTAL_CONFIG_FILE
Path to a declarative configuration file.
.SH EXAMPLES
Run a Python application with the injector active:
.PP
.RS
# (With opentelemetry-injector installed, this happens automatically)
PYTHONPATH=/usr/lib/opentelemetry/python:$PYTHONPATH \\
  OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_PROTOCOL=http/protobuf \\
  OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:4318 \\
  python myapp.py
.RE
.SH NOTES
Python 3.10 or later is required. Earlier versions are detected and skipped
without crashing the instrumented process.
.PP
If the application already carries OpenTelemetry SDK dependencies, the
auto-instrumentation detects this (double-instrumentation check) and
self-deactivates gracefully.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR opentelemetry-injector (8)
.PP
